          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Composition data obtained from Table 2 in Uses of Canola Meal, J. Bonnardeaux, Department of Agriculture and Food, Western Australia, 2007. First, composition data were refered to 1 kg dry mass. Then, C-contents were calculated considering a C-content/dry mass of 46% in carbohydrates (including fibres), 53% in proteins and 75% in fats. All data from "Evolutionary and Biochemical Aspects", A.D. Kay and T. Vrede (in Global Ecology, 2010, Elsevier B.V., S.E. Jørgensen Ed.).</comment>
        </property>
