          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Composition data obtained from Table 2.1 in Utilization of canola seed fractions in ruminant feeds, Master thesis by Ravindra Guptha Heendeniya, University of Saskatchewan (Canada), 2008 (http://library2.usask.ca/theses/available/etd-06162008-141937/unrestricted/THESES_Ravindra_Heendeniya_17_june_2008.pdf). First, composition data were refered to 1 kg dry mass. Then, C-contents were calculated considering a C-content/dry mass of 46% in carbohydrates (including fibres), 53% in proteins and 75% in fats. All data from "Evolutionary and Biochemical Aspects", A.D. Kay and T. Vrede (in Global Ecology, 2010, Elsevier B.V., S.E. Jørgensen Ed.).</comment>
